From University Bookstore Subject Re Ghost on Apple Color user insane In article bettsC Jonathan Betts writes Dear Netters My sister has an Apple Color Display hooked up to an Problem There is an annoying horizontal ghost like stripe that precesses vertically about once per It is about cm She is in grave danger of going insane because of Any ideas of what it might be and how I might cure it for her Joe Betts PS if I pick up the display I thought it might be RFI from the LC it seems to get worse This can be caused by two one of two The first and easiest to fix is interference from something around the monitor such as another monitor or other electrical Try moving the system to another location to fix that Second because of the scan rate of the monitor it tends to synchronize with room lights and can cause the interference you are Try turning off all lights in the room s around the system and see if that If not try moving the system somewhere A third solution would be to get a Apple Color Display It should not have the same problem the Color is more suceptible You can try calling Apple's new support number in the at SOS This number is for ANYONE who has questions regarding Macintosh setup and compatibility and just went into effect for this extended support on Monday April Good luck Kevin Lohman Buyer University Book Store University of Washington Seattle Apple Computers for Education Program